    "narrative": "The Austin Waves offense for April 30 is headlined by **Gunnar Henderson**, who earns our highest efficiency score of 81.88. Facing McCullers Jr. (4.94 xERA), **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from an elite combination of a favorable hitter\u2019s park and a high-volume stolen base environment; the opposing pitcher\u2019s slow delivery (100% stolen base rate) gives us a distinct advantage in our scarcest category. **Jacob Wilson** also presents a strong play (71.63) atop the order, capitalizing on a 10% park factor bump and a favorable matchup against a left-handed arm, which positions him perfectly to accumulate runs and provide the speed necessary to anchor our lineup. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (67.95) remains a must-start, as his xwOBA of .384 and the 12% boost from the matchup against Ober mitigate the risks associated with the right-on-right dynamic.\n\nWhile **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (59.83) sits just on the fringe of our strong-start tier, his massive 14% platoon edge against Peralta proves vital today. We are playing **Nasim Nunez** (45.92) as a tactical pivot; though his score is marginal, the 4% bonus derived from Peralta\u2019s high-frequency base-theft susceptibility makes him an essential \"SB specialist\" play to keep pace in the league standings. **Drake Baldwin** and **Heliot Ramos** (53.50 and 53.76, respectively) round out our lineup as stable, high-floor options. With **Kyle Tucker**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Jackson Merrill**, and **Andy Pages** all unavailable due to scheduled off-days or IL stints, our depth is tested. **Liam Hicks**, **Dominic Smith**, and **Brady House** were considered for the final utility spots, but were ultimately benched in favor of maintaining our current efficiency targets; **Nolan Schanuel** and **Coby Mayo** also narrowly missed the cut as we prioritized the specific stolen base upside offered by **Nasim Nunez**. No weather concerns are currently flagged for the slate, but managers should monitor the lineup status for **Drake Baldwin** and **Nasim Nunez** to ensure no late-scratch defensive replacements dilute their projected plate appearances.",
